## v1.2.0 (2026-06-16)

Minor amendment to State A (stale/superseded) handling. Three additions:

1. **`git cherry` squash-merge false positive + message-search disambiguator.** When a
   branch's PR was squash-merged, `git cherry origin/main <branch>` shows ALL commits with
   a `+` prefix (looks unmerged) and `git rev-list --count origin/main..<branch>` shows
   commits "ahead" — both because squash produces a new commit with a different patch-id
   that cherry's patch-id matching never matches. Relying on either falsely flags subsumed
   branches as unmerged. The reliable disambiguator is message-search on main
   (`git log origin/main --oneline | grep -iE '<distinctive phrase or (#PRnum)>'`),
   cross-checked with `gh pr list --head <branch> --state all`.
2. **Worktree 0-unique-lines redundancy check.** A worktree with "uncommitted modified
   files" can be a false alarm — `diff <(git show origin/main:<path>) <(cat <worktree>/<path>) | grep -c '^>'`
   returning 0 on all files means the work is byte-for-byte already on main.
3. **CC Safety Net destructive-op constraint.** The hook blocks `git checkout -- <file>`,
   `git worktree remove --force`, `git tag -d`, `git branch -D`, `git stash drop`,
   `rm -rf .worktrees/` even with in-conversation user approval; the assistant proves
   safety (subsumed / 0-unique-lines) then hands the exact command to the user.

Three new Failed Attempts rows. Verified this session on HomericIntelligence/ProjectHephaestus:
7 local branches all failed auto-rebase with conflicts and showed every commit as `+` under
`git cherry`, yet message-search proved all 7 subsumed (e.g. `999-fix-pr-thread-reply-mutation`
→ `187720a … (#1041)`; `fix-1282-work` → `22fc435 … (#1282)`; `rc2-conflict-gate` →
`d3701b8 … (#1335)`). Worktree `agent-a7fe2df2b7f6e658b` had 3 modified files all 0-unique-lines
vs main (the `log_on_error` changes shipped via PR #1372). Below: full v1.1.0 skill snapshot.

